BR_text.BRsummary: SC's strange error message after a model is created.
BR_text.BRdescription:
I have a Python script following the user guide for SC:
 <denchmark-link:https://apple.github.io/turicreate/docs/userguide/sound_classifier/>https://apple.github.io/turicreate/docs/userguide/sound_classifier/</denchmark-link>
 
 The script runs through but in the end it throws this error
 <denchmark-code>Exception TypeError: "'NoneType' object is not callable" in <bound method VGGishFeatureExtractor.__del__ of <turicreate.toolkits.sound_classifier._audio_feature_extractor.VGGishFeatureExtractor object at 0x11b1168d0>> ignored
 </denchmark-code>
 
 This error message appears every time as long as a model is created.
 I.e.:
 <denchmark-code>import turicreate as tc
 from os.path import basename
 import sys
 train_set = tc.SFrame('train_set.sframe')
 test_set = tc.SFrame('test_set.sframe')
 
 # Create the model.
 model = tc.sound_classifier.create(train_set, target='category', feature='audio')
 </denchmark-code>
 
 Also produced the same error message in the end.

comments_0.comment_text: This likely has the same root cause as <denchmark-link:https://github.com/apple/turicreate/issues/2842>#2842</denchmark-link>
